  "why": "The paper provides partial diagnostic insight: the authors analyze properties of discovered failures and how they correlate with internal signals (their learned neuron-selection feature weights and correlations between coverage and variety of incorrect labels). They extract which neuron features (e.g., layer position, activation patterns, layers with multiple inputs) are associated with successful failure discovery, and report correlations between coverage and the diversity of labels found. However, they do not trace failures to deeper underlying model vulnerabilities such as biased or corrupted training data, reliance on spurious input features, or specific training/regularization issues, nor do they propose root-cause fixes based on such an analysis. Thus the contribution is characterization/correlation (partial insight) rather than explanation of underlying vulnerabilities (full diagnostic).",
